{
  "answer": "**Chapter 30 of *Diwan-E-Zauq* is titled \"Koi kamar ko tiri kuch jo ho kamar to kahe\".**[^1]\n\nThis is the *matla* (opening couplet) of the ghazal, as is conventional for titling individual poems in Urdu divans.[^2]\n\n[^1]: Sheikh Ibrahim Zauq, *Diwan-E-Zauq*, chapter 30, [translation](https://falsafa-corpus.org/works/sheikh-ibrahim-zauq-diwan-e-zauq-0fa798/30-koi-kamar-ko-tiri-kuch-jo-ho-kamar-to-kahe/translation/).\n\n[^2]: *Ibid.*, [p-bda240](https://falsafa-corpus.org/works/sheikh-ibrahim-zauq-diwan-e-zauq-0fa798/30-koi-kamar-ko-tiri-kuch-jo-ho-kamar-to-kahe/translation/#p-bda240).",
